</blockquote>
<p>In this context, &quot;active&quot; means you are working on the draft and seeking feedback on it. Any draft threads that are no longer in need of critique should have a post from the author stating so. I've edited the above post noting this information.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I'm wishing to post a new post here, a total revamp of the afforementioned 'semi-active' draft. Its here, if you'd like to take a look at the dates and sort.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Given that the thread has a post from less than 14 days ago, and the draft presented is a revision and not an entirely unrelated new premise, it does not merit a new thread. Instead, the author should seek feedback via wikidot PM or the IRC chatrooms.</p>

